Class A_LatitudeLongitude<_SUBTYPE_ extends A_LatitudeLongitude<?>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • cs350s21project.datatype.A_LatitudeLongitude<_SUBTYPE_>
  • Type Parameters:
    _SUBTYPE_ - - the axis subtype: latitude or longitude
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    I_Unitable<_SUBTYPE_>, I_WorldCoordinatable, I_XMLable, java.lang.Comparable<_SUBTYPE_>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Latitude, Longitude
    public abstract class A_LatitudeLongitude<_SUBTYPE_ extends A_LatitudeLongitude<?>>
extends java.lang.Object
implements I_Unitable<_SUBTYPE_>, I_XMLable, I_WorldCoordinatable
    Defines the shared elements of a latitude and longitude in terms of Universal Transverse Mercator (UTM) coordinates. Only northern and western hemispheres are currently supported. Latitude and longitude are mapped onto a square grid, where both dimensions are scaled equivalently; real-world spherical mapping is not used.
